                            <comment id="153400" author="mhanafi" created="Tue, 24 May 2016 20:14:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have the ability to reset min would be all that is need. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any updated on this??&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="140606" author="morrone" created="Sat, 30 Jan 2016 00:50:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the only things that make sense to reset would be the &quot;min&quot; columns.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="140418" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2016 19:18:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ORNL is asking for the same feature. I just inquired about what our staff wants to do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="131210" author="doug" created="Thu, 22 Oct 2015 17:33:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Which specific values in nis and peers would you like to be able to reset?  Things like reference counts and credits cannot be reset as they are values used to manage resources and resetting them would cause resource leaks (and probably trigger asserts).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="128639" author="pjones" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 17:05:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

